$ /dev/fd
-

The directory `/dev/fd` should be symlinked to → Linux/fhs/proc/self/fd

{ /dev/fd/0#fd_0

  → Linux/fhs/dev/stdX#dev_stdin is symlinked to /dev/fd/0

}

{ /dev/fd/1#fd_1

  → Linux/fhs/dev/stdX#dev_stdout is symlinked to /dev/fd/1
}
{ /dev/fd/2#fd_2

  → Linux/fhs/dev/stdX#dev_stderr is symlinked to /dev/fd/2
}


sa:
  → Linux/fhs/dev

  → https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/68681/how-does-having-dev-fd-make-running-shell-scripts-under-sudo-safe[How does having /dev/fd make running shell scripts under sudo safe?]
